e240ca03","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Using both Windows Mobile 6.5 and a 1GHz Snapdragon Processor, this phone can’t help but be fast. But speed isn’t the only thing at which this phone excels. A 16GB microSD card is preloaded to expand the internal memory so now all those photos from your last vacation and the additional contacts from your recently moved-in neighbors will fit perfectly on the amount of space available on your HD2."]},"id":"1d25c101-69b9-40a6-bd01-4df147fe70e1","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Battery Life"},"id":"c0b32ae4-231b-433b-bfa5-d8b41d783d3f","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The HD2 is no dummy and is able to detect its surroundings. The ringer volume level immediately scales down when the phone detects that the call has been picked up. The display also automatically adjusts to the light surroundings and turns off to prevent false screen touches during a call. Whether indoors or outdoors, the weather goes with you no matter where you are. The backscreen on this phone shows the local weather and what to expect in order to avoid being caught in an extreme rainstorm. The phone is built for pure finger-touch control and also has three sensors: G-Sensor, Proximity sensor and an ambient light sensor. And HTC didn’t forget the basics, the HD2 includes Bluetooth, Internal GPS antenna and a digital compass."]},"id":"ef5fdc8c-da28-4d6b-b84f-96ab8c5bb2d1","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"a29568c8-8641-4764-aaf2-da191297ace3","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Even though the size may be hard for some users to grasp (literally), the screen display, vibrant colors and entertainment features may just be the golden ticket with this phone. The HTC HD2 isn’t anything to scream off the rooftops about but it is a considerable option for a sturdy and heavily featured smartphone."]},"id":"ff7ce1ce-f1c8-48f0-874b-1c19237b78d5","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_49650","url":"/htc-hd2-review",